cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Natural Hallucination Analysis"
abstract: >-
  Two implementations of LLM hallucination detection via attention pattern
  analysis. v1 uses Shannon entropy and cross-layer KL divergence with a
  statistical hypothesis test. v2 extends to five feature families
  (entropy, lookback ratio, frequency domain, spectral Laplacian, KL)
  with a trained classifier and self-labeled data pipeline.
authors:
  - family-names: "Kuo"
    given-names: "A"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/A-Kuo/Natural-Hallucination-Analysis"
keywords:
  - hallucination detection
  - attention analysis
  - LLM safety
  - transformer interpretability
  - information theory
